abstract: Isaiah Blackmon scored 17 points and Keith Braxton scored 15 with six rebounds and St. Francis beat William & Mary 78-72 in the DC Holiday Hoops Fest on Sunday.
snippet: Isaiah Blackmon scored 17 points and Keith Braxton scored 15 with six rebounds and St. Francis beat William & Mary 78-72 in the DC Holiday Hoops Fest on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, D.C. — Isaiah Blackmon scored 17 points and Keith Braxton scored 15 with six rebounds and St. Francis beat William & Mary 78-72 in the DC Holiday Hoops Fest on Sunday.
headline_main: Blackmon, Braxton Send St. Francis (PA) Past William & Mary
headline_print_headline: Blackmon, Braxton Send St. Francis (PA) Past William & Mary

abstract: Jordan Burns and Will Rayman each picked up double-doubles, six players reached double-figure scoring and Colgate defeated Columbia 89-71 on Sunday.
snippet: Jordan Burns and Will Rayman each picked up double-doubles, six players reached double-figure scoring and Colgate defeated Columbia 89-71 on Sunday.
lead_paragraph: HAMILTON, N.Y. — Jordan Burns and Will Rayman each picked up double-doubles, six players reached double-figure scoring and Colgate defeated Columbia 89-71 on Sunday.
headline_main: Burns, Rayman Double-Double, Colgate Tops Columbia 89-71

abstract: Christians in the Gaza Strip will be allowed to visit holy cities such as Bethlehem and Jerusalem at Christmas, Israel authorities said on Sunday, reversing a decision not to issue them permits.
snippet: Christians in the Gaza Strip will be allowed to visit holy cities such as Bethlehem and Jerusalem at Christmas, Israel authorities said on Sunday, reversing a decision not to issue them permits.
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Christians in the Gaza Strip will be allowed to visit holy cities such as Bethlehem and Jerusalem at Christmas, Israel authorities said on Sunday, reversing a decision not to issue them permits.
headline_main: Israel Reverses Ban, Gaza Christians Can Visit Christmas Sites
headline_print_headline: Israel Reverses Ban, Gaza Christians Can Visit Christmas Sites

abstract: In 2019, Hollywood put out a whopping 58 franchise films, including “The Rise of Skywalker,” released this weekend. Still, ticket sales dropped.
snippet: In 2019, Hollywood put out a whopping 58 franchise films, including “The Rise of Skywalker,” released this weekend. Still, ticket sales dropped.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Cue the sad trombone: Movie ticket sales in the United States and Canada will total roughly $11.45 billion for the year, a 4 percent decrease from 2018.
